## Streaming

Nanobridge supports `stream: true`. If Cursor exposes streaming for your setup, enable it to reduce time-to-first-token.

SDK example:

```python
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY", base_url="https://api.nanobridge.net/v1")
stream = client.chat.completions.create(
    model="deepseek-v4-flash",
    messages=[{"role": "user", "content": "Explain this function"}],
    stream=True,
)
for chunk in stream:
    if chunk.choices[0].delta.content:
        print(chunk.choices[0].delta.content, end="")
```

